# Cursor AI Rules for Flora MCP Server

## CRITICAL: Read These Files Every Session Start

Before doing ANY work in this repository, you MUST read:
1. /FLORA_DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md
2. /SKILLS.md

This applies even after context compaction or when resuming work.

## Railway Deployment Protocol (Mandatory)

Before making ANY Railway-related changes:
1. Read /FLORA_DEVELOPMENT_RULES.md (if not read this session)
2. Read /SKILLS.md (if not read this session)
3. Identify last working commit: `git log --oneline -5`
4. Compare your changes with working baseline: `git diff 9dc71f6 <file>`
5. Verify alignment with working configuration
6. Test locally before deploying

## Last Known Working Configuration
- Commit: 9dc71f6
- Check if this is still current: `git log --oneline -1`

## Pre-Deployment Checklist

Always verify:
- [ ] No EXPOSE or HEALTHCHECK in Dockerfile
- [ ] PORT fails fast in production (src/config/index.js)
- [ ] Error handlers after microservice.initialize() (server.js)
- [ ] All route handlers have `next` parameter (src/index.js)
- [ ] Compared with git diff 9dc71f6
- [ ] Syntax check passed: `node --check server.js`

## Never Skip These Steps

Even for "quick fixes" or "small changes" - always follow the protocol.
Past failures were caused by skipping these steps.
